Pull an image from a registry
 - docker pull myimage:1.0
 
Push an image to a registry
 - docker push myrepo/myimage:2.0
 
How to get into the Docker Terminal 
 - docker exec -i -t my-nginx-1 /bin/bash

Build an image from the Dockerfile in the current directory and tag the imageâ€¨
 - docker build -t myimage:1.0

List the running containers
 - docker container ls

Delete all running and stopped containers
 - docker container rm -f $(docker ps -aq)
 
Delete stopped containers
 - docker container prune

Cleans up dangling images, containers, volumes, and networks (ie, not associated with a container)
 - docker system prune -a
 
Get logs from container
 - docker logs <container_name>
 
List the docker networks
 - docker network ls
 
You can see more details on the network associated with Docker using network inspect command.
 - docker network inspect <networkname>
 
shows the resource utilization (CPU, memory, etc...) of running containers
 - docker stats
 
Create Volume 
 - docker volume create <volume name>
 
Check the volume created 
 - docker volume ls
 
inspect volume, check volume, read data from volume, inspect data locally
 - docker volume inspect <volume name>
 
Deleting a volume
 - docker volume rm <volume name>
 
Removing all unused volumes
 - docker volume prune
 
 
